posts.title: Well I Got THE CALL Twice
posts.content:
I have lived in Virginia since 2017. I got a political polling call twice recently and I am wondering if VA is up for grabs? I have never gotten poll calls before in my life and I’m old. I am registered to vote but haven’t registered to any political party (Dem, Rep or Independent) in 27 years.

7/30/24 Was an Asian man who knew my name. I didn’t care. The call lasted 24 minutes and 41 seconds. He then hung up on me right after he asked me if I was very likely, somewhat likely, neutral, unlikely, highly unlikely etc to vote for DJT because the Republicans were going to cut Social Security. I responded: “That is a lie and his questions were formatted to either skew the polls or misinform me to affect my vote”. Funny thing is right before he disconnected he said we were about half way through. He also had used an area code (607) that matched mine even though I hadn’t lived in that area since 2016. To tell you the truth I’m surprised he lasted as long as he did. His number came back as a low spam risk.

9/3/24 Was a call from a black woman who had a Pennsylvania area code. Her questions were more general in nature and she was quick. The call lasted 8 minutes and 25 seconds. She ended the call by asking me when I was going to vote (early or 11-5-24 in person)? I found that a little strange So I checked my voter status and took a screenshot of it just in case I run into any issues on Election Day. This number came back as a high spam risk.
